            <entry xml:id="entry_arc" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>arc</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>arcæ</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>копье</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>spear</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>nyjjarc wyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>пуститься ввысь</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>устремиться</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                    <abv:exampleGrp>
                        <abv:example>
                            <quote>bæxtæ qæwtæm nyjjarc sty, sæ xæʒærttyl fæpyrx væjjync</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>лошади устремились в селения, разбежались по своим домам</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>horses rushed to the villages, run away to their homes</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"
                                    /><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>
                        </abv:example>
                    </abv:exampleGrp>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>arc badyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>становиться стоймя, дыбом</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (о волосах)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about hair)</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>rise</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (о волосах)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about hair)</note></sense>
                    <abv:exampleGrp>
                        <abv:example>
                            <quote>mæ cæstytæ axæm cæwyldær anyʒævdysty, æmæ mæ særy q˳yntæ arc
                                abadtysty</quote>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>я заметил („мои глаза коснулись“) что-то такое, что волосы у меня
                                    стали дыбом</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>I noticed (“my eyes touched”) something that made my hair
                                    rise</q>
                            </abv:tr>
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"
                                    /><biblScope>115—116</biblScope></bibl>
                        </abv:example>
                    </abv:exampleGrp>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>cʼæx zældæbæl saw bæxgintæ, ewguræj dær arcægintæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на зеленом лугу черные всадники, все — с копьями</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>there are black horsemen on a green meadow, all with spears</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Totyraʒ Soslany jæ arcy fynʒyl felvæsta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Тотраз поднял Сослана на острие копья</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Totraz raised Soslan to the point of a spear</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>330</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>læg æ bæxi raǧi xusgæ cæwuj æ bæxarcæ ba zænxæbæl lasuj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>человек спящий едет на коне, а пику волочит по земле</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a sleeping man is riding a horse, and is dragging a peak along the
                                ground</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dæ særy astæw су xæssys? bīræǧ maræn cʼæx ærcytæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>что ты несешь посредине головы? для умерщвления волка серые копья</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>what are you carrying in the middle of your head? gray spears for
                                killing the wolf</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            164</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Oc. %iarc%i через *%iarsc%i восходит к %iaršti%i, с закономерным
                    переходом зубного %it%i перед %ii%i в аффрикат, как в <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_k0yʒ"/> и др.: <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hälsti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>ašc</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aršti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>arsti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ṛṣṭi-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ašteay</w></mentioned> (из иранского). Названия холодного оружия в
                    осетинском относятся, как правило, к иранскому фонду; ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7rdyn"/> ‘лук’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fat"/>
                    ‘стрела’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kard"/> ‘нож’, %iæxsargard%i ‘шашка’,
                    ‘меч’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wart"/> ‘щит’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 142</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>40</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 155, 207, 214</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1956, стр. 40</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1956, p. 40</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Ossetic %iarc%i through *%iarsc%i traces back to %iaršti%i, with
                    a regular transition of dental <c>t</c> into affricate before <c>i</c>, like in
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0yʒ"/> etc.: <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>hälsti</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="zkh"><lang/>
                        <w>ašc</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>aršti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>arsti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>ṛṣṭi-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>ašteay</w></mentioned> (from Iranian). The names of blade weapons in
                    Ossetic usually refer to the Iranian resources; cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7rdyn"/> ‘bow’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fat"/> ‘arrow’,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kard"/> ‘knife’, %iæxsargard%i ‘sword’,
                    ‘sabre’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wart"/> ‘shield’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 142</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>40</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 155, 207, 214</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSOAS"
                            /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1956, стр. 40</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">1956, p. 40</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
